From fa4f9ff8cc888b85e76cb9c39849d7886aaa1db8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 15:37:19 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 144/174] x86/mm: MMUPAGE-granular hint + result handling in
 arch_get_unmapped_area

Under PGCL the mmap address space is MMUPAGE-granular: vm_unmapped_area()
returns an address aligned to MMUPAGE_SIZE (the hardware page), which need
not be PAGE_SIZE-aligned, and mmap hint addresses arrive in MMUPAGE units
(mmap2 offset is MMUPAGE-granular, and info.align_offset is already built
with MMUPAGE_SHIFT here).

Three sites in arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c still used PAGE_ granularity:

  - arch_get_unmapped_area() rounded the hint up with PAGE_ALIGN(),
    over-aligning a valid MMUPAGE hint.
  - arch_get_unmapped_area_topdown() masked the hint with PAGE_MASK,
    discarding sub-PAGE-but-MMUPAGE-aligned bits.
  - arch_get_unmapped_area_topdown() validated the vm_unmapped_area()
    result with `!(addr & ~PAGE_MASK)`.  A legitimate MMUPAGE-aligned
    result then looked like an error: the function fell through to the
    bottom-up path (or hit VM_BUG_ON(addr != -ENOMEM) under DEBUG_VM).

The DEBUG_VM crash reproduced as

  kernel BUG at arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c:230!
  arch_get_unmapped_area_topdown+0x356
  __get_unmapped_area <- map_vdso <- load_elf_binary <- kernel_execve

during PID 1's first execve at PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4.  With DEBUG_VM off the
same path silently fell back to bottom-up, masking the bug in matrix runs.

Switch all three to MMUPAGE_ALIGN/MMUPAGE_MASK.  Each is identity at
PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0 (MMUPAGE_SHIFT==PAGE_SHIFT==CONFIG_PAGE_SHIFT), so the
Newton-limit baseline is unchanged.  Compile-verified at PAGE_MMUSHIFT=0
and =4.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c | 15 ++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c b/arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c
index c8b2f330811c..07f77c7a660c 100644
--- a/arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kernel/sys_x86_64.c
@@ -141,7 +141,8 @@ arch_get_unmapped_area(struct file *filp, unsigned long addr, unsigned long len,
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
 	if (addr) {
-		addr = PAGE_ALIGN(addr);
+		/* PGCL: hint addresses are MMUPAGE-granular (identity at shift 0) */
+		addr = MMUPAGE_ALIGN(addr);
 		vma = find_vma(mm, addr);
 		if (end - len >= addr &&
 		    (!vma || addr + len <= vm_start_gap(vma)))
@@ -187,7 +188,8 @@ arch_get_unmapped_area_topdown(struct file *filp, unsigned long addr0,
 
 	/* requesting a specific address */
 	if (addr) {
-		addr &= PAGE_MASK;
+		/* PGCL: hint addresses are MMUPAGE-granular (identity at shift 0) */
+		addr &= MMUPAGE_MASK;
 		if (!mmap_address_hint_valid(addr, len))
 			goto get_unmapped_area;
 
@@ -225,7 +227,14 @@ arch_get_unmapped_area_topdown(struct file *filp, unsigned long addr0,
 		info.align_offset += get_align_bits();
 	}
 	addr = vm_unmapped_area(&info);
-	if (!(addr & ~PAGE_MASK))
+	/*
+	 * PGCL: vm_unmapped_area() returns an MMUPAGE-granular address; a valid
+	 * result need not be PAGE_SIZE-aligned, so test alignment with
+	 * MMUPAGE_MASK (identity at PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0).  Using PAGE_MASK here made
+	 * valid MMUPAGE-aligned results look like errors -> silent bottom-up
+	 * fallback (and VM_BUG_ON under DEBUG_VM).
+	 */
+	if (!(addr & ~MMUPAGE_MASK))
 		return addr;
 	VM_BUG_ON(addr != -ENOMEM);
 
